article.description: Raemond Robinson scored 14 points off the bench and led five players in double figures as Charleston Southern beat Toccoa Falls of the National Christian College Athletic Association 101-54 on Sa
article.headline: Charleston Southern beats Toccoa Falls of the NCCAA 101-54
article.linkText: Charleston Southern beats Toccoa Falls of the NCCAA 101-54
article.story: CHARLESTON, S.C. -- Raemond Robinson scored 14 points off the bench and led five players in double figures as Charleston Southern beat Toccoa Falls of the National Christian College Athletic Association 101-54 on Saturday night. Robinson was 5 of 8 from the field including four 3-pointers for the Buccaneers (3-2). Cortez Mitchell and Patrick Wallace added 11 points apiece and Christian Keeling and Armel Potter had 10 points apiece. Robinson sank a 3-pointer and followed with a layup to shake off a slow start for the Buccaneers and put them on top 14-12 with 15:03 to play in the first period. They led the rest of the way and had a 51-31 advantage at the break. The Buccaneers averaged 57.5 percent shooting from the field, 40 percent from the free throw line, and had a 53-28 rebounding edge over Toccoa Falls. Cameron Williams led the Eagles with 15 points and six boards.
